cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Processing tasks such as word embeddings and language models. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the methodology for distilling relational knowledge from a pre-trained language model. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the ability of language models to capture semantic and syntactic relationships. It could also be classified under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves finding relevant sentences from a large text corpus. Finally, it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves fine-tuning a language model.
